cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a new kernel-based stochastic gradient descent algorithm for model selection and optimization. This algorithm is related to online learning theory for unconstrained settings, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of the algorithm for image classification (cs.CV) and regression tasks (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper uses standard smoothness assumptions on the target function, which is related to optimization (cs.DS) and neural networks (cs.NE).
